<DOC><DOCNO> AP891218-0141 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-18-89 1940EST</FILEID><FIRST>r w AM-Bush-Personnel     12-18 0126</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Bush-Personnel,110</SECOND><HEAD>Bush Names 4 Officials to King Holiday Commission</HEAD><DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   President Bush has decided to name four topgovernment officials to be members of the Martin Luther King Jr.,federal holiday commission in 1990.   They are Secretaries Jack Kemp of HUD and Lauro Cavazos ofEducation, and William J. Bennett, director of National DrugControl Policy and Constance B. Newman, director of the Office ofPersonnel Management.   Bush also intends to nominate former Air Force Secretary EdwardC. Aldridge Jr., to the president's national securitytelecommunications advisory committee, and Paul F. Oreffice to theadvisory committee for trade policy and negotiations.   Oreffice, president and chief excutive officer of the DowChemical Company in Midland, Mich., is being reappointed to atwo-year term.</TEXT></DOC>